### ViTale Authentication API Tests
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api/v1
@email = test{{$randomInt}}@example.com
@password = SecurePass123!

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 1. Register New Account
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 2. Register with Weak Password (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "weak{{$randomInt}}@example.com",
  "password": "weak",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 3. Register with Invalid Email (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "notanemail",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 4. Register Duplicate Email (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 5. Login Without Email Verification (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 6. Verify Email (Replace TOKEN with actual token from email/logs)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email?token=REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 7. Login After Verification (Should Succeed)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 8. Login with Wrong Password (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "WrongPassword123!"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 9. Forgot Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 10. Reset Password (Replace TOKEN with actual token from email/logs)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePass456!"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 11. Login with New Password
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}",
  "password": "NewSecurePass456!"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 12. Resend Verification Email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/resend-verification
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email}}"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### 13. Refresh Token (Replace JWT with actual token from login response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Cookie: vitale_jwt=REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_JWT

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Test Password Strength Requirements
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Missing uppercase letter (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test1@example.com",
  "password": "securepass123!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### Missing lowercase letter (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test2@example.com",
  "password": "SECUREPASS123!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### Missing number (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test3@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### Missing special character (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test4@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### Too short (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test5@example.com",
  "password": "Sec1!",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### OAuth Tests
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Google OAuth Login (Open in browser)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/login/google

### Facebook OAuth Login (Open in browser)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/login/facebook

### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Edge Cases
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### Register with disposable email (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@tempmail.com",
  "password": "{{password}}",
  "fullName": "Test User"
}

### Forgot password for non-existent email (Should succeed with generic message)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "nonexistent@example.com"
}

### Reset password with expired token (Should Fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "expiredtoken123456789012345678901",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePass789!"
}
